WEBVTT

00:00:01.524 --> 00:00:03.857
Languages don't just die naturally.

00:00:04.706 --> 00:00:07.777
People abandon mother tongues,
because they're forced to.

00:00:08.651 --> 00:00:10.851
Often, the pressure is political.

00:00:11.781 --> 00:00:13.177
In 1892,

00:00:13.201 --> 00:00:15.447
the US Army general Richard Henry Pratt

00:00:15.471 --> 00:00:17.979
argued that killing indigenous cultures

00:00:18.003 --> 00:00:20.891
was the only alternative
to killing indigenous people.

00:00:21.863 --> 00:00:24.545
"Kill the Indian," he said,
"but save the man."

00:00:25.688 --> 00:00:28.908
And until 1978,
the government did just that,

00:00:28.932 --> 00:00:32.187
removing indigenous children
from their families